# Engineering Daily Standup

Date: 2026-07-01
Department: Engineering
Attendees: Daniel Chen, Priya Sharma, Maya Johnson

## Issues Addressed

- Checkout payments showed intermittent failures in the US region after the payment gateway routing change.
- The failure rate was highest for saved-card transactions.
- Security confirmed there was no evidence of credential misuse.

## Decisions

- Treat the checkout payment issue as high priority because it directly affects revenue.
- Daniel Chen will lead technical investigation with the payments platform owner.

## Action Items

- Create a high-priority Jira ticket for payment gateway investigation.
- Attach checkout error samples, affected region, and saved-card failure pattern to the ticket.
- Update Customer Success before the next customer escalation review.

